  "title": "ðŸ“Š Introduction to Microsoft Excel",
  "description": "Learn the fundamentals of Microsoft Excel, the world's most popular spreadsheet application. Master basic operations and start creating powerful spreadsheets.",
  "metadata": {
    "duration": "25 minutes",
    "difficulty": "Beginner",
    "prerequisites": []
  },
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Microsoft Excel is a powerful spreadsheet application used for data analysis, calculations, and creating professional reports. In this lesson, you'll learn the essential skills to get started with Excel."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Learning Objectives"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "Understand the Excel interface and basic navigation",
          "Learn to enter and edit data in cells",
          "Master basic formatting techniques",
          "Create simple formulas and calculations",
          "Save and manage Excel files"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Getting Started with Excel"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Opening Excel"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "There are several ways to open Microsoft Excel depending on your setup."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "**From Start Menu**: Click Start and search for Excel",
          "**From Desktop**: Double-click the Excel icon",
          "**From Office.com**: Visit office.com and launch Excel Online"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Understanding the Interface"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Familiarize yourself with the main components of the Excel interface."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": {
        "headers": ["Component", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["**Ribbon**", "Tabs with commands organized by function"],
          ["**Formula Bar**", "Shows cell contents and formulas"],
          ["**Worksheet**", "Grid where you enter data"],
          ["**Status Bar**", "Displays information about selected cells"],
          ["**Name Box**", "Shows the address of the active cell"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Basic Operations"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Entering Data"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Learn how to enter different types of data in Excel cells."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Text**: Click a cell and type",
          "**Numbers**: Enter numerical values",
          "**Dates**: Use date formats (MM/DD/YYYY)",
          "**Formulas**: Start with = sign"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Keyboard Shortcuts"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": {
        "headers": ["Shortcut", "Action"],
        "rows": [
          ["`Ctrl + C`", "Copy"],
          ["`Ctrl + V`", "Paste"],
          ["`Ctrl + X`", "Cut"],
          ["`Ctrl + Z`", "Undo"],
          ["`Ctrl + S`", "Save"],
          ["`F2`", "Edit cell"],
          ["`Enter`", "Move down"],
          ["`Tab`", "Move right"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Practice Exercise"
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "data": {
        "title": "Create Your First Spreadsheet",
        "description": "Practice your new Excel skills by creating a simple budget spreadsheet.",
        "steps": [
          "Open Excel and create a new workbook",
          "Enter column headers: Item, Cost, Quantity, Total",
          "Add some sample data (e.g., Coffee, $3.50, 2)",
          "Create a formula to calculate totals",
          "Format the spreadsheet with basic styling",
          "Save the file with a descriptive name"
        ],
        "checklist": [
          "Headers are clearly formatted",
          "Sample data is entered correctly",
          "Formula calculates totals properly",
          "File is saved with appropriate name",
          "Spreadsheet looks professional"
        ],
        "estimatedTime": "15 minutes",
        "difficulty": "beginner"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Next Steps"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "In the next lesson, you'll learn:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Formulas and Functions** - Advanced calculations",
          "**Data Formatting** - Making spreadsheets look professional",
          "**Charts and Graphs** - Visualizing your data",
          "**Data Management** - Sorting and filtering"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "content": "**Remember**: Practice regularly to become comfortable with Excel!"
    }
  ]
} 